 Eibar have announced the signing of 22-year-old right-back Alvaro Tejero from Real Madrid on a five-year contract. Tejero joined Madrid’s youth set-up back in 2005 but only went on to make one league appearance for the club, coming off the bench to make his debut back in 2017 according to goal.com. He spent last season on loan with Albacete in the Segunda Division, and joins for a fee thought to be around €3 million (£2.7m/$3.4m). The post Eibar Sign Tejero From Madrid  Source: Independent